.Dd April 18, 1994
.Dt BASENAME 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm basename
.Nd return filename portion of pathname
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm basename
.Ar string
.Op Ar suffix
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm Basename
deletes any prefix ending with the last slash
.Ql \&/
character present in
.Ar string ,
and a
.Ar suffix ,
if given.
The resulting filename is written to the standard output.
A non-existent suffix is ignored.
.Pp
.Sh EXAMPLES 
The following line sets the shell variable
.Ev FOO
to
.Pa ls .
.Pp
.Dl FOO=`basename /usr/bin/trail`
.Pp
.Sh DIAGNOSTICS
The
.Nm basename
utility
exit 0 on success, and >0 if an error occurs.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr dirname 1 ,
.Xr csh 1 ,
.Xr sh 1
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm basename
utility conform to
.St -p1003.2-92 .
